1 § 4652. AGRICULTURAL LAND TRANSFER ASSISTANCE PROGRAM
2 The Agricultural Land Transfer Assistance Program is established at the
3 Agency of Agriculture, Food and Markets to:
4 (1) identify agricultural land in the State that may be available for
5 transfer or succession;
6 (2) provide farm owners with assistance in succession planning or
7 finding willing purchasers who will maintain the land for farming;
8 (3) assist new farmers in accessing capital or financing to purchase
9 agricultural land;
10 (4) connect owners of agricultural land with purchasers willing to retain
11 the land for farming; and
12 (5) implement the assistance, tools, and programs established under this
13 chapter.
14 § 4653. FARM OWNERSHIP SUCCESSION PLANNING
15 (a) The Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets, after consultation with
16 the Secretary of Commerce and Community Development, shall establish the
17 Farm Ownership Succession Planning Program to provide farmers assistance
18 with planning for succession of ownership of agricultural land.
19 (b)(1) As part of the Program, the Secretary shall develop a succession
20 planning toolkit that can be used by farm owners who are planning on selling
21 or closing their farm. The toolkit shall include the following:
