2 farmers interested in purchasing or leasing agricultural land.
3 (d) The Secretary shall train Agency staff or contract for services to aid
4 farmers exiting farming and those beginning farmers navigate the land transfer
5 process with the tools and resources available under the Program. These
6 persons shall be known as land transfer navigators, and they shall be available
7 to meet with prospective sellers and purchasers individually to facilitate lands
8 transfers that maintain agricultural land for farming. Land transfer navigators
9 shall also provide assistance to sellers and purchasers regarding the regulatory
10 requirements related to land transfer and related to the ownership or operation
11 of a farm, such as compliance with the Required Agricultural Practices.
12 § 4654. AGRICULTURAL LAND PORTAL
13 The Secretary shall develop an agricultural land portal as an online tool on
14 the Agency’s website that allows persons seeking to sell agricultural land to
15 connect with persons seeking to purchase agricultural land. The tool shall
16 include those public postings of agricultural land available for sale or lease,
17 and instructions on how prospective purchasers can connect with sellers.
18 § 4655. LAND TRANSFER AND SUCCESSION BOARD
19 (a) Creation. There is created the Land Transfer and Succession Board,
20 which for administrative purposes shall be attached to the Agency of
21 Agriculture, Food and Markets.
