1 (b) Organization of Board. The Board shall be composed of:
2 (1) the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets or designee;
3 (2) a representative of the Vermont Farm and Forest Viability Program
4 at the Vermont Housing and Conservation Board, appointed by the Speaker of
5 the House;
6 (3) a representative of the Vermont Land Trust, appointed by the
7 Committee on Committees;
8 (4) a representative of Land for Good, appointed by the Speaker of the
9 House; and
10 (5) a representative of the Vermont Farm to Plate Initiative, appointed
11 by the Committee on Committees.
12 (c) Member terms. The members of the Board shall be appointed for terms
13 of three years or until the member’s earlier resignation or removal. A vacancy
14 shall be filled by the appointing authority for the remainder of the unexpired
15 term. An appointed member shall serve not more than three consecutive three-
16 year terms.
17 (d) Powers. The Board shall:
18 (1) assist the Secretary of Agriculture, Food and Markets with
19 implementation of the requirements of this chapter, including fundraising and
20 development of expertise in land succession or acquisition; and
