4 (e) Officers; committees. The Board may elect officers, establish one or
5 more committees or subcommittees, and adopt procedural rules as it shall
6 determine necessary and appropriate to perform its work.
7 (f) Quorum; meetings; voting. A majority of the sitting members shall
8 constitute a quorum, and action taken by the Board may be authorized by a
